  • @ACheck(name="Suspicious usage of OPEN DATASET",
        description="<p>When used with the addtion FILTER, OPEN DATASET allows to execute any operating system command. Thus, the FILTER addtion should be avoided in general. The <a href=\"https://help.sap.com/abapdocu_750/en/abenabap_system_commands_appl_sxpg.htm\">SXPG framework</a> should be used for OS calls instead.</p>",
        groupName="Security",
        languages=ABAP,
        parameters=ABSTRACT_SYNTAX_TREE)
public class OpenDatasetWithFilterAdditonCheck
extends EntityCheckBase
    Checks for usages of OPEN DATASET with FILTER addition - see ABAP keyword documentation. Allowed operating system commands can be specified in a whitelist.
